script = ExtResource("3_1tugy")
category = 1
text = "The battle at Bullgrave is the infamous historical Sugori battle from 13 years ago. It is referred to as the most important Civil War battle in its history and the bloodiest fight at that. Bullgrave is an island near the border of the Sugori Isles that was picked on by infamous Mid-East criminal Scareye, captain of the terroristic pirate group the Scareye Pirates. Despite the responces being quite swift from the Sugori people, it still ended up quite bloody.

The battle began lasting what was a long 16 hours, the main forces in this fight were simply Sugori pirates and army members, versus the Scareye Pirates. Scareye was spotted by scout ships going towards Bullgrave with 20+ ships, Sugori responded immediately. Eventually the Sugori found out that Scareye was trying to take over this area of the Isles with him and 6 of his El Capitanos. Meanwhile, Sugori arrived with the showing of 3 Giras as Wester Banks was not in the country, Army Second-in-Command Mina Elroark, Saint Joloise Vector Barbossa, both King Joloise, at the time up-and-coming Giras Morgan Pikefist and Yves von Eric, and many more Joloise and Minor Captains. It was a vigourous battle, causing both sides to tire out a lot, but the battle was won by Sugori with a decent chunk of casualties, but nothing like what the Scareye Pirates suffered. 

The Scareye Pirates lost 3 El Capitanos, but all 6 were injured to a variety, one had to leave his duties due to the severity of it. Those 20+ ships only were a total of 9 on the retreat, but scouts are convinced that not so many made it back in one piece. The Sugori meanwhile lost major players in local reputations, with the biggest being Eugene Trossard, a Joloise captain and Vanessa's heavy candidate for a future Gira. Many Joloise crews lost members and some captains, the event was so shocking it caused Jill Patel to not recover mentally and retire at a slightly early age for a Gira. The many that died were mourned but celebrated, as the Sugori remain a show of equality and clan culture because of the sacrifice of those gone.On Bullgrave Day every year, people around the whole island remember what happened and wish for it never again but are glad for those who bravely stepped up. On the other hand, Scareye's appearances dwindled and even though it was apparent he restructured his cabinet of Capitanos after the incident, it was less than a decade before rumours of his death began.

Although it was mostly naval combat, there was oppurtunity for more close quarter brawls. There were many notable match ups during the battle that are hard to imagine today. 66 year old Jay Rocks held his own against the up-and-coming rookie El Capitano named Bloodking Emrys who was at the time 19 years old. Yves von Eric fought and killed Orlac Shutzer who was their 2nd Base Commander. Morgan Pikefist saw his brother Elliot but could not get revenge in time before Gus stopped his ship and caused a retreat. Gus and Gorgan Birchwind, both ex-Great Fumbrian Pirates under captain Jay Rocks reunited whilst seiging a ship. The final straw was when Scareye himself ended up in a fight against an ex-friend of his back from the Defense of Wotopolis, Patty Vulcna, a captain of the Joloise Crew from Wotopolis that he helped defend with Vector Barbossa. He won against Patty, but she was only thrown into the sea whilst Scareye retreated due to damage on his ship and his remaining fleet followed. "
id = 53
name = "Bullgrave Incident"
gdscript = ExtResource("1_yipn8")
